8th March

This meme relates to me because I feel pretty and coquette after drinking Coke Zero instead of Regular coke due to Coke Zero containing zero calories and sugar. I personally love Kanye and Drake memes because rappers are well known for their hyper masculinity while these memes are edited to make them appear as feminine and cute which contrasts their aesthetic intensely. The purpose of this meme was to express how I feel when I choose to consume less sugar over a regular version of drink with high sugar content.

library(magick)
square <- image_blank(width = 300, 
                    height = 90,
                    color = "#fff") %>%
  image_annotate(text = " When I drink Coke Zero \n instead of Regular Coke",
                 color = "#000",
                 size = 25)

kanye<-image_read("kanye2.jpg")%>%
  image_scale(300)

top = c(square) %>%
  image_append()

bottom = c(kanye) %>%
  image_append

meme <- c(top, bottom) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

meme

image_write(meme, "meme.png")

This gif was a combination of multiple memes of Kanye and Drake looking feminine and coquette. This gif is a visualization of how I feel in certain situations which I think it really shows my personality/idnetity.

library(magick)

# read images
frame1 <- image_read("kanye.jpg")%>%
  image_scale(500)
frame2 <- image_read("kanye2.jpg")%>%
  image_scale(500)
frame3 <- image_read("kanye3.jpg")%>%
  image_scale(500)
frame4 <- image_read("drake.jpg")%>%
  image_scale(500)
frame5 <- image_read("kittydrake.jpg")%>%
  image_scale(500)
frame6 <- image_read("sillydrake.jpg")%>%
  image_scale(500)

# Resize images
resized_frame1 <- image_scale(frame1, "500x500")
resized_frame2 <- image_scale(frame2, "500x500")
resized_frame3 <- image_scale(frame3, "500x500")
resized_frame4 <- image_scale(frame4, "500x500")
resized_frame5 <- image_scale(frame5, "500x500")
resized_frame6 <- image_scale(frame6, "500x500")

# Combine images into a sequence
meme_sequence <- image_append(c(resized_frame1, resized_frame2, resized_frame3, resized_frame4, resized_frame5, resized_frame6))

# Display the result
image_browse(meme_sequence)

# putting the frames in order using a vector
frames <- c(resized_frame1, resized_frame2, resized_frame3, resized_frame4, resized_frame5, resized_frame6)

# creating an animation
frames %>%
  image_animate(fps = 1)

# image write
image_write(frames, "animation.R")
